The following is an example of Select N correct of M tool, in this case the
No of 3. The // indicates a comment
----------------------------
//HIN  No Hint unless you un-comment this text make it into a hint. 
//EXP  No Explanation unless you un-comment the text and write a hint.
/IMP "../Tools/Prob#Val_3"
// line above gives a problem it number and value (here 3 points)
// ../CAPA/MCTools/i3p5 3 items 5 properties. Change `3' in  Prob#Val_3 for 
// desired points. 
Some Text Here... Match each  person  with the appropriate description. (If the first  corresponds to B, and the next 2 to C,  enter BCC) 
// NOTE: I this problem, there will be 3 `items', and for each
//  the student must identify a coresponding `property'
// The properties here are tp1, tp2....tp5. and are "Poet", "Painter"
// "Politician", "Philosopher", "Philanthropist"
// For each item, the code is prepared for a max of 4 variations.
// s1a, s1b, s1c, and s1d are variations of
// item 1. For less than 4 variation, EDIT the mix_ statements. (For 2
// variations, FILL IN  s1a and s1b, and EDIT mix1 to read: 
// /LET mix1=random(1,2,1)
// WRITE the correct integer each variation: set x1a=1 for the tp1 property,
// x1a=2 if it corresponds to tp2, etc.. Then x1b= 1 If tp1 is the answer,
//  etc.....  NOTE: not all properties listed  need be used but all
// must be filled in.
//--------------------------------PROB.START--------------------------------
/IMP "../Tools/Prob#Val_3"
// ../CAPA/MCTools/Nof3 3 Statements;  Change `3' in  Prob#Val_3 for desired 
// points. 
Replace the text here with the Problem Narrative. (Give ALL correct answers, i.e., B, AC, BCD...) 
// FILL IN the statements below. s1a, s1b, s1c, and s1d are variations of
// statement 1. There may be 1, 2, 3 or 4 variations of each statement. 
// For more than 1 variation, EDIT the mix_ statements. (i.e., get two
// variations of statement1, FILL IN  s1a and s1b, and EDIT mix1 to read: 
// /LET mix1=random(1,2,1)
// set a1a = 1 for a correct variation, and 2 for incorrect, etc..
// ALL variations for at least one statement must always be correct!
//  For variations not used, leave '26' as the integer.
//
/LET s1a="Statement 1a"
/LET s1b="Statement 1b"
/LET s1c="Statement 1c"
/LET s1d="Statement 1d"
/LET mix1=random(1,1,1)
/LET a1a=1
/LET a1b=26
/LET a1c=26
/LET a1d=26
//
/LET s2a="Statement 2a"
/LET s2b="Statement 2b"
/LET s2c="Statement 2c"
/LET s2d="Statement 2d"
/LET mix2=random(1,1,1)
/LET a2a=2
/LET a2b=26
/LET a2c=26
/LET a2d=26
//
/LET s3a="Statement 3a"
/LET s3b="Statement 3b"
/LET s3c="Statement 3c"
/LET s3d="Statement 3d"
/LET mix3=random(1,1,1)
/LET a3a=1
/LET a3b=26
/LET a3c=26
/LET a3d=26
//
/IMP "../MCtools/Nof3aux"
/ANS(Nof3right)
